programme.title: I Was Actually There - Nicky Winmar's Stand Against Racism

programme.title: An Unquiet Grave
programme.desc: A year after Jamie's wife tragically died in a car accident, he persuades her sister, Ava, to accompany him to the accident site to perform a peculiar ritual. As the night progresses, it becomes evident that Jamie harbours sinister motives.

Her friends Zurina, Wati, and Ustaz join forces to end her suffering, but a malevolent demon interrupts their efforts. Will Azlinda succeed in severing the cursed ties that bind her, or is she destined to remain trapped in darkness forever?

programme.title: Get in the Dark
programme.desc: A reporter hears three horror stories when investigating a case of the paper doll spirit 20 years ago. Miss Qiao had died in vain then, and her butler paid a paper craftsman to make a paper doll to be buried with her. Miss Qiao’s spirit is revived to take revenge when the doll’s eyes are drawn, and a series of horrible events begins to happen...

programme.title: They Wait in the Dark
programme.desc: Amy and her adopted son Adrian flee from her abusive ex-girlfriend Judith. Seeking refuge in an abandoned farmhouse in Amy's Kansas hometown, they confront a supernatural evil force from her dark past that haunts Adrian. As Judith pursues them, Amy and Adrian must face the dangers both outside and within the house.

programme.title: The Fox Demon Love
programme.desc: Adapted from a story in the novel “Strange Tales from Liaozhai”, a young student in the late Ming Dynasty meets a charming fox demon and they soon fall in love. Though they encounter several obstacles due to their different nature, the lovers continue to fight against fate. Can they finally be together?

programme.title: Paper Man

programme.desc: On the menu: lamb's lettuce salad with confit Jerusalem artichokes and oven-roasted cauliflower with vanilla sauce. Discovery of the day: organic maple syrup and its amazing by-products...

programme.title: La Photographe
programme.desc: France, 1936. The German photojournalist Gerta Pohorylle and her partner, the Hungarian photographer Andre Friedmann, had a hard time getting published in the press. When the Spanish Civil War broke out, they were determined to cover the events, under the names of Gerda Taro and Robert Capa.

programme.title: Sur La Dalle
programme.desc: Adamsberg and Mathieu are sure: a serial killer is on the loose. They need to identify his motive to catch him before he can do any more harm. The key to the enigma is closely linked to regional folklore. Lying on a dolmen, Adamsberg uses his imagination to find the solution.

programme.title: Tendance XXI
programme.desc: Les Journees Particulieres by LVMH: perspectives for the craft professions in the world of fashion. The story of sauerkraut, a journey from China to Alsace. Graphic artist Sarah Naud and her sculptures in cement. How to get the biker look. Dgena Mouclier and upcycled menswear fashion.

programme.title: Disparition Inquietante
programme.desc: Lino and Norma are a happy couple. But when Norma goes to the maternity hospital to give birth, she disappears. Despite all their differences Iris Koben heads the investigation with Samuel Camurat. The pressure is on: Norma's life and that of her baby are in danger.

programme.title: Rassemblance
programme.desc: At 17, fleeing the Taliban, Rohullah Hossiny travels through Iran, Turkey, and Greece before arriving in Belgium. In Brussels, thanks to the Duo for a job association, he finds a mentor and joins Corica, where he becomes a master roaster. In turn, he trains other exiles.
